.TH "fc_copy_buffer_to_sglist" 9 "fc_copy_buffer_to_sglist" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fc_copy_buffer_to_sglist \- This routine copies the data of a buffer into a scatter-gather list (SG list).
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u32" fc_copy_buffer_to_sglist
.BI "(void *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ","
.BI "struct scatterlist *sg "  ","
.BI "u32 *nents "  ","
.BI "size_t *offset "  ","
.BI "u32 *crc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buf" 12
pointer to the data buffer.
.IP "len" 12
the byte-length of the data buffer.
.IP "sg" 12
pointer to the pointer of the SG list.
.IP "nents" 12
pointer to the remaining number of entries in the SG list.
.IP "offset" 12
pointer to the current offset in the SG list.
.IP "crc" 12
pointer to the 32-bit crc value.
If crc is NULL, CRC is not calculated.
